---
title: Turkey Pomodoro Penne Bake with Mozzarella & Herbed Ricotta
description: No matter the weather, it’s pretty much impossible not to daydream about cheesy baked carbs. Luckily, this dish is guaranteed to make those dreams come true. In it, you’ll find penne and zucchini layered with herby, creamy ricotta and a rich marinara sauce. To top things off, there’s a melty blanket of mozzarella. Serve it right from the dish for maximum cheese pull potential and wait for the oohs and aahs from your lucky fellow diners.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/673b8e11fd3e9058428acb69-f16e2cc7.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/67631c1e10495c1449a76cf0-en-US.pdf
time required: 45 minutes
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 1020 kcal
  fat: 48 g
  saturated fat: 17 g
  carbohydrates: 92 g
  sugar: 23 g
  protein: 50 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 990 mg
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/turkey-pomodoro-penne-bake-67631c1e10495c1449a76cf0
cuisine: Southern Europe
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Bring a #medium pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and dice @onion{1/2}(peeled and diced) (whole onion for 4 servings). Finely dice @tomato{1}(finely diced). Trim @zucchini{1}(trimmed), then grate on the largest holes of a #box grater{}.

Once water is boiling, add @penne pasta{6%oz} to #pot{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until almost al dente, ~{8%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in Step 6).

Drain penne. (Keep empty pot handy for Step 5.)

Pat @ground turkey{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add turkey in a single layer; season with a big pinch of salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of olive oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add diced onion, tomato, and a pinch of salt. Cook, stirring occasionally, until onion is softened, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in @marinara sauce{5%oz}, zucchini, @veggie stock concentrate{2}, @tomato paste{1}, 1/2 tsp @Italian seasoning{1%tbsp}, 3/4 cup water, 1 1/2 tsp sugar, 2 tsp olive oil, and 3/4 tsp salt. (For 4 servings, use 1 tsp Italian Seasoning, 1 1/2 cups water, 3 tsp sugar, 4 tsp olive oil, and 1 1/2 tsp salt.) Bring to a simmer; cook, stirring, ~{3%minutes} more. Turn off heat.

> Use pan used for turkey here.

While sauce simmers, in a #medium bowl{}, combine @ricotta cheese{4%oz}, 1/2 tsp Italian seasoning (1 tsp for 4 servings), and a drizzle of olive oil. (Use the rest of the Italian seasoning as you like.) Season with salt and pepper.

Add drained penne, sauce, and @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) to pot used for pasta. Season with salt and pepper; stir to thoroughly combine.

Spread out half the pasta mixture in an #8-by-8-inch baking dish{}. (For 4, use a 9-by-13-inch baking dish.) Using a #tablespoon{}, dollop pasta mixture with herbed ricotta. Top with remaining pasta mixture, then sprinkle with @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}.

> Stir turkey into pot along with drained penne.

Cover #baking dish{} with #foil{}. (TIP: Coat inside of foil with nonstick spray first to prevent sticking.) Bake pasta on top rack for ~{10%minutes}, then remove from oven; discard foil.

Heat broiler to high. Broil until cheese is lightly browned, ~{4-5%minutes}. TIP: Watch carefully to avoid burning.

Let cool slightly; top with @?chili flakes{1%tsp} if desired. Divide between plates and serve.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.